322
00:14:40,475 --> 00:14:44,701
In this entire struggle, many people 
didn't participate in this movement.

323
00:14:44,701 --> 00:14:46,157
Which is understandable.

324
00:14:46,157 --> 00:14:50,717
Not everyone dares to raise their 
voice against the people in power.

325
00:14:51,144 --> 00:14:52,616
But there were some people who

326
00:14:52,616 --> 00:14:54,566
were bootlicking the British so much that

327
00:14:54,566 --> 00:14:58,881
they were supporting the British 
in ending the Quit India Movement.

328
00:14:58,881 --> 00:15:00,906
There were two major organizations at that time.

329
00:15:00,906 --> 00:15:02,910
Muslim League and Hindu Mahasabha.

330
00:15:02,910 --> 00:15:05,845
The Muslim League passed a resolution in 1940

331
00:15:05,845 --> 00:15:08,050
which is known as the Lahore Resolution.

332
00:15:08,050 --> 00:15:10,118
Because of this, they demanded

333
00:15:10,118 --> 00:15:12,863
that a separate country be created for Muslims.

334
00:15:12,863 --> 00:15:15,142
It is also called the Pakistan Resolution.

335
00:15:15,142 --> 00:15:17,506
At that time, there was a Muslim League leader Fazlul Huq,

336
00:15:17,506 --> 00:15:20,700
he was the first Prime Minister of Bengal Province.

337
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:24,736
Their government in Bengal was formed 
with an alliance with the Hindu Mahasabha.

338
00:15:24,736 --> 00:15:26,474
In this Muslim League government,

339
00:15:26,474 --> 00:15:30,830
Dr Shyama Prasad Mukherjee was the Finance Minister.

340
00:15:30,830 --> 00:15:33,263
It was on 26 July 1942,

341
00:15:33,263 --> 00:15:35,323
about two weeks before the start of the Quit India Movement.

342
00:15:35,323 --> 00:15:38,630
Syama Prasad Mukherjee wrote a letter to the British government.

343
00:15:38,630 --> 00:15:39,951
"Anybody who, during the war,

344
00:15:39,951 --> 00:15:41,227
plans to stir up mass feelings, 

345
00:15:41,227 --> 00:15:43,879
resulting in internal disturbances or insecurity

346
00:15:43,879 --> 00:15:45,379
must be resisted by the government."

347
00:15:46,035 --> 00:15:50,820
Further, he asked about how the Quit India 
Movement could be combated in Bengal.

348
00:15:50,820 --> 00:15:53,111
He states that the administration should be such that

349
00:15:53,111 --> 00:15:55,628
all efforts by the Congress would fail.

350
00:15:55,628 --> 00:15:58,462
And the movement would not begin in the Bengal Province.

351
00:15:58,462 --> 00:16:02,053
He was, literally, discussing ideas with the British government

352
00:16:02,053 --> 00:16:04,146
on how to suppress this movement.

353
00:16:04,146 --> 00:16:06,740
During the 24th session of the Hindu Mahasabha in Kanpur,

354
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:09,233
their party leader Vinayak Damodar Savarkar

355
00:16:09,233 --> 00:16:11,153
came up with another strategy.

356
00:16:11,153 --> 00:16:15,294
The Hindu Mahasabha follows 
the strategy of responsive cooperation.

357
00:16:15,294 --> 00:16:18,723
Not only did they intend to give 
unconditional cooperation to the British government,

358
00:16:18,723 --> 00:16:21,515
they were also ready for active and armed resistance.

359
00:16:21,999 --> 00:16:24,087
At that time, the Hindu Mahasabha was a political party

360
00:16:24,087 --> 00:16:25,331
and at the organizational level,

361
00:16:25,331 --> 00:16:29,504
RSS had the same response towards the Quit India Movement.

362
00:16:29,504 --> 00:16:32,100
That's why the British intelligence agencies

363
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:35,084
described their stance as follows.

364
00:16:35,084 --> 00:16:39,960
"The Sangh has scrupulously kept itself within the law,

365
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:43,942
and...refrained from taking part in the 
disturbances that broke out in August 1942."

366
00:16:43,942 --> 00:16:48,000
While on one hand, Netaji Subhash Chandra Bose formed the Azad Hind Fauj

367
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,318
a few months after the Quit India Movement,

368
00:16:49,318 --> 00:16:52,071
On the other hand, Savarkar was helping the colonial government

369
00:16:52,071 --> 00:16:54,909
recruit hundreds of thousands of Indians

370
00:16:54,909 --> 00:16:56,948
in the British Armed Forces.

371
00:16:56,948 --> 00:16:59,320
These Indians joined the British Army

372
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:02,265
and fought against Subhash Chandra Bose's Azad Hind Fauj.

373
00:17:02,265 --> 00:17:04,221
At that time, there was a man named Narayan Apte

374
00:17:04,221 --> 00:17:06,164
who joined the British Army

375
00:17:06,164 --> 00:17:09,805
and later on, became a recruiter for 
the British Royal Indian Air Force.

376
00:17:09,805 --> 00:17:11,763
Later on, he was found guilty

377
00:17:11,763 --> 00:17:14,547
for being involved in the assassination of Mahatma Gandhi.

378
00:17:14,547 --> 00:17:18,040
Along with that, Nathuram Godse's 
brother, Gopal Godse

379
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:20,101
was also fighting this war on the British side.

380
00:17:20,101 --> 00:17:23,029
Savarkar had said some more things 
about the Quit India Movement.

381
00:17:23,029 --> 00:17:25,173
That this type of unscrupulous rebellion 

382
00:17:25,173 --> 00:17:27,190
did not deserve any sympathy.

383
00:17:27,190 --> 00:17:30,638
This was a huge insult to the freedom fighters

384
00:17:30,638 --> 00:17:33,527
who were actually fighting 
against the British at that time.

385
00:17:33,527 --> 00:17:37,054
And that is why, after hearing this, Netaji 
Subhash Chandra Bose could not remain silent.

386
00:17:37,054 --> 00:17:38,967
On 14th August 1942,

387
00:17:38,967 --> 00:17:42,339
in Berlin, he sent a message through the radio.

388
00:17:42,339 --> 00:17:45,964
"I would request Mr. Jinnah, Mr. Savarkar, and all those leaders

389
00:17:45,964 --> 00:17:48,894
who still think of a compromise with the British

390
00:17:48,894 --> 00:17:52,194
to realise (that).... in the world of tomorrow 
there will be no British Empire."

391
00:17:52,194 --> 00:17:55,582
A senior leader of Hindu Mahasabha, N.C. Chatterjee wrote,

392
00:17:55,582 --> 00:17:56,958
"It is rather amusing to find

393
00:17:56,958 --> 00:17:58,631
that Mr. Jinnah wants

394
00:17:58,631 --> 00:18:02,008
the Muslims to not join the Congress movement

395
00:18:02,008 --> 00:18:04,415
and Mr. Savarkar wants

396
00:18:04,415 --> 00:18:05,945
Hindus not to join the same."

397
00:18:05,945 --> 00:18:07,634
Despite all this opposition, friends,

398
00:18:07,634 --> 00:18:10,779
the Quit India Movement was successful.

399
00:18:10,779 --> 00:18:13,706
The world started talking about India's freedom.

400
00:18:13,706 --> 00:18:17,727
The then American President Roosevelt 
also put pressure on the UK government

401
00:18:17,727 --> 00:18:20,064
to fulfil some of India's demands.

402
00:18:20,064 --> 00:18:25,908
Even in Britain, the British people were 
demanding that India be given freedom.

403
00:18:25,908 --> 00:18:30,164
In June 1945, the British Labour Party 
released its new manifesto.

404
00:18:30,164 --> 00:18:31,863
Let Us Face The Future.

405
00:18:31,863 --> 00:18:33,689
They made a promise to the British people

406
00:18:33,689 --> 00:18:35,752
that if they came into power

407
00:18:35,752 --> 00:18:39,521
then they would give complete freedom to colonies like India.

408
00:18:39,521 --> 00:18:43,281
Next month, in 1945, the Labour Party came to power in Britain

409
00:18:43,281 --> 00:18:46,202
and the new Prime Minister was Clement Attlee.

410
00:18:46,202 --> 00:18:48,027
And he openly declared that

411
00:18:48,027 --> 00:18:51,560
it was time to give India self-governance.

412
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:53,728
As soon as the government changed in Britain,

413
00:18:53,728 --> 00:18:57,283
the arrested Congress leaders 
were released from jail in India.

414
00:18:57,283 --> 00:19:02,338
And two years after that, the struggle that 
our Indian freedom fighters started years ago,

415
00:19:02,338 --> 00:19:04,023
became successful.

416
00:19:04,023 --> 00:19:07,240
India got complete freedom.

417
00:19:16,099 --> 00:19:18,772
Although it was clear by 1945 that

418
00:19:18,772 --> 00:19:20,857
India's freedom was inevitable,

419
00:19:20,857 --> 00:19:23,979
in 1946, two other important things happened,

420
00:19:23,979 --> 00:19:27,376
which increased the importance of freedom.

421
00:19:27,376 --> 00:19:29,712
First, the INA soldiers' court-martial,

422
00:19:29,712 --> 00:19:31,061
also known as the INA trials,

423
00:19:31,061 --> 00:19:34,068
and second, the Royal Indian Navy Mutiny.

